description: {"blocks":[{"key":"8e3k8","text":"This landscape study aims to assess the current state of the recreational diving industry in French Polynesia, particularly from a local community perspective. The main focus of study will be to investigate local perceptions of industry. Particularly:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":160,"length":91}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5lc7i","text":"The perceived impact on the local community – whether positive or negative","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":74}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4cnif","text":"The perceived presence or absence of local participation – motivators and deterrents such as existing barriers to entry in the industry","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":135}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7ssnd","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cskme","text":"To achieve the aims outlined, this study will also need to investigate the wider context of the French Polynesian recreational dive industry – information about which seems to be lacking in current literature.
